	<h1 id="main-heading">KRS ยง 189.830 - Use of emblem of reflective tape restricted; exemption from requirement</h1>

	<ol class="flow law-definitions">
		<li>(1) The slow-moving vehicle emblem shall be restricted to the uses specified herein and the use on any other type of vehicle or on other objects is prohibited.</li>
		<li>The slow-moving vehicle emblem shall not be required on trailers or other drawn vehicles which do not obstruct the slow-moving vehicle emblem required on the towing vehicle.</li>
		<li>Highway construction or maintenance vehicles and public utility vehicles shall not require slow-moving vehicle emblems when being guarded by flagmen or flares.</li>
		<li>The use of slow-moving vehicle emblems or alternative reflective tape, as required under KRS 189.820, shall be in addition to any other reflective or lighting devices required by law.</li>
		<li>The slow-moving vehicle emblem shall not be used on a bicycle.</li>
	</ol>

